SIMPLE: juicer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: juicer
<hw>juicer</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a utensil with a conical
ridged center that is used for squeezing juice fro citrus
fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> reamer, juice reamer.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A state of drunkenness; <as>as, to throw on a
<ex>juicer</ex>; to have a <ex>juicer</ex> on all night</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An habitual drunkard; one who drinks alcoholic
beverages frequently to the state of inebriation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Juiciness</ent>⟦br⟧
